contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:23.093 --> 01:26.828
- Sheila, what is all this?
- A power breakfast.

01:26.863 --> 01:28.663
And it looks delicious,

01:28.698 --> 01:30.777
but you know I usually like to
eat light in the morning.

01:30.801 --> 01:35.003
Just a bowl of Fiber One, or--
- Oh, I know, Louis.

01:35.038 --> 01:38.373
I also know the day
you take control of the firm

01:38.408 --> 01:39.941
is no usual day.

01:39.976 --> 01:41.976
Before I take control
of what now?

01:42.012 --> 01:44.779
Louis, you just merged,
which means it's time

01:44.815 --> 01:47.449
for a new king
to claim the throne.

01:47.484 --> 01:49.662
All right, Sheila, if you're
saying what I think you are,

01:49.686 --> 01:51.653
Harvey's already
managing partner,

01:51.688 --> 01:54.030
and Zane's going to fight
to take it from him.

01:54.031 --> 01:57.891
Which sets the table for you
to take it from both of them.

01:57.892 --> 02:01.293
Louis, you're a king.

02:01.329 --> 02:05.731
And we should all
be kissing your ring.

02:05.766 --> 02:08.100
But, Sheila,
where is all this coming from?

02:08.136 --> 02:10.603
It's coming from the fact
that Harvey left you

02:10.638 --> 02:13.873
to fight off the hordes,
and you did just that

02:13.908 --> 02:16.542
by subjugating the army
of Robert Zane.

02:16.577 --> 02:18.444
- I suppose I did.
- No supposing, Louis.

02:18.479 --> 02:21.413
You're a god.
A Viking god.

02:21.449 --> 02:23.849
And Viking gods
take what they want.

02:23.885 --> 02:26.285
Now go in there,
and claim what's yours.

02:26.320 --> 02:29.155
I will, but not until
I claim what's also mine--

02:29.774 --> 02:31.073
Not yet.

02:31.109 --> 02:33.676
Let's do it this afternoon,
afterward.

02:33.711 --> 02:37.379
Then we can play
"managing partner/secretary."

02:37.415 --> 02:38.892
In that case you'd better
be ready to take

02:38.916 --> 02:41.617
a whole lot of dictation.

02:41.652 --> 02:43.886
Oh, I will.
Now go.

02:43.921 --> 02:46.756
And return to me a king.
- I know.

03:08.452 --> 03:12.320
- Morning, Robert.
- Harvey, I just got in.

03:12.356 --> 03:16.091
The sign looks good.
- Good, I'm glad you liked it.

03:16.126 --> 03:18.260
You ready to do this thing?

03:18.295 --> 03:20.128
If you mean,
am I ready to get back to being

03:20.164 --> 03:22.097
a managing partner,
I sure as hell am.

03:22.132 --> 03:23.765
Then give me
your John Hancock,

03:23.801 --> 03:26.435
I'll get it to Louis,
and you will officially be

03:26.470 --> 03:29.438
the managing partner
by the end of the day.

03:30.474 --> 03:32.708
Harvey Specter?

03:32.743 --> 03:35.377
That's right, this is
my partner, Robert Zane.

03:35.412 --> 03:37.179
My partner and I
were clients of Mike Ross.

03:37.214 --> 03:40.582
We founded Pod Space.
- You must be Max Louden.

03:40.617 --> 03:42.384
How do you know I'm not Nick?

03:42.419 --> 03:45.087
Because Mike said if one
of you ever came to see me,

03:45.122 --> 03:46.122
it'd be you.

03:46.156 --> 03:48.957
So why don't you tell me
what the problem is,

03:48.992 --> 03:50.258
and I'll get you out of it.

03:50.294 --> 03:52.861
Oh, I hope it's that easy.

03:52.896 --> 03:55.130
Nick and I started
another business venture.

03:55.165 --> 03:58.166
Raised 100 million to
get the thing off the ground.

03:58.657 --> 04:00.256
I can only account
for 50 of it.

04:00.292 --> 04:01.858
Well, when 50 million
is missing,

04:01.893 --> 04:03.760
the math adds up
to embezzlement.

04:03.795 --> 04:06.429
I know that, but I'm telling
you, Nick wouldn't do that.

04:06.464 --> 04:08.031
Not to me,
and not to the business.

04:08.066 --> 04:09.632
Then if he didn't take it,
he got taken.

04:09.668 --> 04:11.601
Look, I don't know
what happened.

04:11.636 --> 04:14.270
But what I do know is that if
we can't account for the money,

04:14.306 --> 04:16.906
and anyone finds out,
we're not just out of business;

04:16.942 --> 04:19.175
we're in prison.
- Trust me, Max.

04:19.211 --> 04:21.244
I'm not going
to let that happen.

04:21.279 --> 04:23.046
Thank you.

04:25.359 --> 04:26.692
And, Max,

04:26.728 --> 04:29.495
don't tell Nick
you came to me with this.

04:29.530 --> 04:33.365
Well, I wasn't going to, but
do you mind if I ask why not?

04:33.401 --> 04:35.101
I don't want him
to know I'm coming.

04:38.864 --> 04:41.398
I know you already know this,
but he's either guilty

04:41.433 --> 04:42.477
and trying
to pin it on his partner,

04:42.501 --> 04:43.300
or it's the other way around.

04:43.335 --> 04:44.835
No way that kid's guilty.

04:44.870 --> 04:46.314
I don't know that,
and neither do you.

04:46.338 --> 04:47.838
I know you're
managing partner,

04:47.873 --> 04:50.407
but you handle your clients,
and I'll handle mine.

04:50.442 --> 04:53.510
Hey, fair enough, but just
to be clear, we just merged.

04:53.545 --> 04:55.645
We need to keep
every client we've got.

04:55.681 --> 04:57.314
Like I said, Robert.

04:57.349 --> 05:00.450
You handle your clients,
I'll handle mine.

05:05.470 --> 05:06.328
I've got an assignment
for you.

05:06.329 --> 05:08.130
Oh, good morning, Robert.
You look nice today too.

05:08.131 --> 05:09.864
Hey, you get to work on time,

05:09.900 --> 05:11.077
I'll tell you that necklace
is pretty all you want.

05:11.101 --> 05:12.033
Right now, I need you
to look into

05:12.069 --> 05:13.309
one of
Harvey Specter's clients.

05:13.337 --> 05:16.104
Let me get this straight.
I just finished tussling

05:16.139 --> 05:18.473
with the guy over sticking my
nose into one of his clients,

05:18.508 --> 05:19.941
and now you want me
to stick my nose

05:19.977 --> 05:21.710
into another one
of his clients?

05:21.745 --> 05:24.646
Samantha,
the man needs your help.

05:24.681 --> 05:25.992
And besides,
he's already seen the bad.

05:26.016 --> 05:27.160
It's time to show him the good.

05:27.184 --> 05:29.351
And again,
what exactly is the good

05:29.386 --> 05:30.819
of me horning in
on his territory?

05:30.854 --> 05:32.721
The good is for the firm.

05:32.756 --> 05:35.457
He may not see it now,
but he will.

05:35.492 --> 05:38.833
- Okay, give it to me.
- He's got two young bucks.

05:38.834 --> 05:40.328
One of them
is up to something shady.

05:40.364 --> 05:42.430
I don't know which one,
but he has a soft spot

05:42.466 --> 05:44.099
for the one named Max.

05:44.515 --> 05:46.615
If that guy's wrong,
he's not going to see it.

05:46.650 --> 05:48.528
And no matter what, we can't
afford to lose the client,

05:48.552 --> 05:50.819
because we just merged.
- Exactly.

05:50.855 --> 05:52.688
I knew I keep you around
for a reason.

05:52.723 --> 05:54.289
That you do.

05:54.325 --> 05:57.059
Now, what's the
"something shady"?

05:57.094 --> 06:00.062
- $50 million is missing.
- Ooh, that sounds fun.

06:00.097 --> 06:01.330
So you're on it?

06:01.365 --> 06:02.509
Oh, I'm more
than on it, Robert.

06:02.533 --> 06:03.882
I know exactly what to do.

